text.section:
A carrier shall make a reasonable disclosure in its solicitation and sales materials of:
the provisions that relate to the carrier's right to change premium rates, including any factors that may affect the changes in premium rates;
the provisions that relate to renewability of policies and contracts;
the provisions that relate to preexisting conditions; and
the provisions of § 15-1209 of this subtitle that require an employer to make dependent coverage available to eligible employees but do not require the employer to make a contribution to the premium payments for that dependent coverage.
